	<region id="editorData">
		<node id="editorData">
			<attribute id="HowToTrigger" type="LSString" value="Repro steps:&#xD;&#xA;1. Start the game&#xD;&#xA;2. loadlevel WLD_Main_A&#xD;&#xA;3. oe qnight NIGHT_OwlbearCubDog_902e10f8-e9d8-4eb6-ac0f-9ad8ba8787ed&#xD;&#xA;4. End the day and go to camp&#xD;&#xA;5. Go to sleep, the dialog will start" />
			<attribute id="needLayout" type="bool" value="False" />
			<attribute id="nextNodeId" type="uint32" value="388" />
			<attribute id="synopsis" type="LSString" value="The player hears an uproar in the camp and  think the owlbear’s turned on Scratch. When they investigate, they discover the cub is having a nightmare and the dog is comforting him. The player can talk to them and confirm that there's no danger. Subsequently, the cub will be a permanent feature in the camp, with new behaviours with Scratch, plus a new default dialogue.&#xD;&#xA;Note: if the player decides to not investigate the sounds, the animals will be moved off-stage for the remainder of the night/the sounds will stop, The player won't know what happened until they see the animals again. If they have SwA, they can learn that there was nothing wrong." />
